In this directory, there are dumps of all 'lookup' tables in application. If you
are changing those, you must include it in UPDATING file and create appropriate
dumps of tables do it is easy to recovery. Dumps are easy to create and load. In
console:

for dumping:

File.open('_dumpfile_.yml', 'w') {|out| YAML.dump(_DumpedClass_.find(:all), out)

for loading:

File.open('_dumpfile_.yml', 'w') {|out| yaml.load(out)}.each {|obj| obj.create}

When changing column name preffered way is to create dump and then loadit
through modification block like this:

File.open('_dumpfile_.yml', 'w') {|out| yaml.load(out)}.each do |obj|
        new_obj = _ModifiedClass_.new
        new_obj.attributes = obj.attributes
        new_obj._new_attribute_ = obj._old_attribute
        new_obj.save
end
